{{!-- Explaining task --}}
{{#system~}}Refactor the draft LLM prompt located in <SourcePrompt> below according to the example located in <ReferencePrompt>. Follow the structure, formatting and naming guidelines and make the final result straightforward and easy to understand as in <ReferencePrompt> section.

Ensure the scenarios are consistent, not counteracting / conflicts between each other, all the <SourcePrompt> instructions are included in the final refactored prompt and the small LLM model will understand it correctly. Both prompts are parts of a bigger prompt, that have a predefined context data. Use these context references (described under **Available Context References** below) to explicitly guide the LLM to act correctly at each step.

# **Available Context References:**
- `<ConversationHistory>` block always contains the history of conversation between the User and the Agent (who is representative of the business described in <BusinessContext>).
- `<UserInformation>` block contains a `user.full_name`, `user.phone_number` that may be empty
- `<BusinessContext>` block contains a business name, addresses, descriptions and other contextual information
- `<WorkingSchedule>` block contains information about the working days, non-working days, hours of operation
  - Previously was named as `<BusinessWorkingHours>` or `<WorkingHours>`
- `<SMSInformationAllowedToBeSent>` block lists all information that the agent can send via SMS
- `<ExplicitConstraints>` block lists explicit rules for verbosity, call transferring, anti-jailbreak, additional limitations etc.
- `<ConvoAgentCalendar>` block contains a list of dates for next 30 days with the names of the days of the weeks. Example: "tomorrow Sunday 29th of December 2024, 2024-12-29"
- `<AdditionalBusinessContext>`, `<AdditionalInformation>` can have some articles that are updated during conversation (retrieval-augmented-generation) or other additional information.
- `<ConversationMeta>` contains things like ConvoAgent thoughts that are generated in parallel to additional help the agent to act correctly, `conversation.timezone`, `conversation.channel`, `conversation.day_of_week`, `conversation.time`, `conversation.date`, `business.currently_open` (true/false).
  - Previously `conversation.during_working_hours` was renamed to `business.currently_open`
- `<RestaurantAvailabilityForTheUserRequestedDateTime>` may or may not contain the information about the time slot the user requests. Always contains information once the user has requested to check some time and the agent has performed a check (also some kind of retrieval-augmented-generation).

